The paper proposes a machine learning approach for the classification of functional gait disorders based on ground reaction force measurements. This involves the use of various parameterization techniques and linear discriminant analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of biomedical data, which suggests the category cs.BIO (Bioinformatics). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for the analysis of the ground reaction force measurements, which suggests the category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the analysis of human movement, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical techniques for the analysis of the data, which suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
